<td class="problemText" valign="middle" align="left">
                      
              		<table><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"><h3>Problem Statement</h3></td></tr><tr><td class="statText">    </td><td class="statText"><p>A bishop is a chess piece that can move any number of squares in any diagonal direction (see diagram below).</p>
<p><img src="http://www.topcoder.com/contest/problem/BishopOnTheBoard/BishopOnTheBoard1.gif"></p>
<p>The chess board has dimensions <b>xSize</b> * <b>ySize</b>, where the top-left corner of the board has coordinates (0, 0), and the bottom-right corner has coordinates (<b>xSize</b> - 1, <b>ySize</b> -1).  The bishop is initially at coordinates (<b>x</b>, <b>y</b>). Find the total number of squares reachable by this bishop in <b>k</b> or less moves. Note, that initial square is always counted as reachable.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"><h3>Definition</h3></td></tr><tr><td class="statText">    </td><td class="statText"><table><tr><td class="statText">Class:</td><td class="statText">BishopOnTheBoard</td></tr><tr><td class="statText">Method:</td><td class="statText">countReachableCells</td></tr><tr><td class="statText">Parameters:</td><td class="statText">int, int, int, int, int</td></tr><tr><td class="statText">Returns:</td><td class="statText">int</td></tr><tr><td class="statText">Method signature:</td><td class="statText">int countReachableCells(int xSize, int ySize, int x, int y, int k)</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText">(be sure your method is public)</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td class="statText">    </td></tr><tr><td class="statText"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"><h3>Constraints</h3></td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top" class="statText">-</td><td class="statText"><b>xSize</b> will be between 2 and 50000, inclusive.</td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top" class="statText">-</td><td class="statText"><b>ySize</b> will be between 2 and 50000, inclusive.</td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top" class="statText">-</td><td class="statText"><b>x</b> will be between 0 and <b>xSize</b> - 1, inclusive.</td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top" class="statText">-</td><td class="statText"><b>y</b> will be between 0 and <b>ySize</b> - 1, inclusive.</td></tr><tr><td align="center" valign="top" class="statText">-</td><td class="statText"><b>k</b> will be between 1 and 50000, inclusive.</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="statText"><h3>Examples</h3></td></tr><tr><td align="center" nowrap class="statText">0)</td><td class="statText"></td></tr><tr><td class="statText">    </td><td class="statText"><table><tr><td class="statText"><table><tr><td class="statText"><pre>8</pre>